#function that takes in list of strings and returns clean
def clean_text(my_list):
    for i in range(len(my_list)):
        my_list[i] = my_list[i].replace('\n','')
        my_list[i] = my_list[i].replace('\xa0','')
        my_list[i] = my_list[i].replace('                  ',' ')
        my_list[i] = re.sub(r'\[[0-9]\]','',my_list[i])
        my_list[i] = my_list[i].lower()
        my_list[i] = re.sub(r'^\[(.*?)\]','',my_list[i])
    return my_list
lc['lewis_entry'] = clean_text(lc['lewis_entry'])
lc['clark_entry'] = clean_text(lc['clark_entry'])

Add word count¶

In [586]:
#get word count for each lewis entry
lc['lewis_entry'] = lc['lewis_entry'].fillna("")
word_count = []
for i in lc['lewis_entry']:
    wc = 0
    wc = len(i.split())
    word_count.append(wc)
lc['lewis_word_count'] = word_count

#get word count for each clark entry
lc['clark_entry'] = lc['clark_entry'].fillna("")
word_count = []
for i in lc['clark_entry']:
    wc = 0
    wc = len(i.split())
    word_count.append(wc)
lc['clark_word_count'] = word_count

Split dataframe by season¶

In [587]:
# split by season
seasons = []
for i in lc['date']:
    if i.month > 8 and i.month <12:
        seasons.append("fall")
    elif i.month == 12 or i.month <3:
        seasons.append("winter")
    elif i.month >= 3 and i.month <6:
        seasons.append("spring")
    else:
        seasons.append("summer")
lc['season'] = seasons

Word Clouds¶

In [597]:
#create lewis word cloud
filteredWords = []
tokenizer = RegexpTokenizer(r'\w+')
stopWords = set(stopwords.words('english'))
wordy = []
for i in range(len(lc['lewis_entry'])):
    wordy += tokenizer.tokenize(lc['lewis_entry'][i])
    for w in wordy:
        if w not in stopWords:
            filteredWords.append(w)

word_freq_dist = nltk.FreqDist(w for w in filteredWords)
wordcloud = WordCloud(width=1000, height=500).generate_from_frequencies(word_freq_dist)
plt.figure(figsize=(20,10), facecolor='k')
plt.imshow(wordcloud)
plt.axis("off")
plt.savefig('lewis_wordcloud.png', facecolor='k', bbox_inches='tight')

Sentiment Analysis¶

In [633]:
l_zen = []
l_subj = []
l_sent = []
for i in range(len(lc['lewis_entry'])):
    l_zen.append(TextBlob(lc['lewis_entry'][i]))
for i in l_zen:
    if i == "":
        l_sent.append(None)
        l_subj.append(None)
    else:
        l_sent.append(i.sentiment[0])
        l_subj.append(i.sentiment[1])
lc['lewis_entry_sentiment'] = l_sent
lc['lewis_entry_subjectivity'] = l_subj
